# C++ Coding Style (Rewrite)

Applies to `next/nlrc_vksplat/` only. Keep rules binary and checkable.

## Files and layout

- Use **`.hpp`** for headers and **`.cpp`** for sources — never `.h` or `.c`
- **`#pragma once`** in every header
- Namespace **`nlrc::vksplat`** for library code (`nlrc::vksplat::shaders` for embedded SPIR-V)
- Paired TUs: `foo.hpp` + `foo.cpp`; declarations in hpp, definitions in cpp (templates / header-only `constexpr` in hpp when required)
- No **`using namespace`** in headers

```cpp
// BAD — ref-style header name in rewrite
#include "buffer.h"

// GOOD
#include "buffer.hpp"
```

## Naming (clang-tidy SSOT: `next/nlrc_vksplat/.clang-tidy`)

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Namespace | `lower_case` | `nlrc::vksplat` |
| Types / structs / enums | `CamelCase` | `TensorBwdConfig`, `SortingKey` |
| Functions / locals / parameters | `snake_case` | `tensor_bwd_shared_memory` |
| Private/protected members | `snake_case` + `_` | `buffer_` |
| Compile-time constants | `k` + `CamelCase` | `kTileSize`, `kSmokeSpirv` |
| Enum constants | `CamelCase` | `PipelineStage::ProjectionForward` |

Forbidden in new code:

- Ref-style `*_t` type aliases (`sortingKey_t`) — use `using SortingKey = ...`
- camelCase free functions (`tensorBwdSharedMemory`)

## const and constexpr

- **`const` by default**: immutable locals, `const&` for read-only inputs, `const` member functions when state is not modified
- **`constexpr` when compile-time**: `inline constexpr` for constants (`kFoo`), `constexpr` for pure functions evaluable at compile time
- **`nullptr`** for null pointers — never `NULL` or `0`

```cpp
// BAD
char* version();
int tile_size = 16;

// GOOD
[[nodiscard]] const char* version();
inline constexpr int kTileSize = 16;
```

## Macros

Allowed:

- `VKSPLAT_*` in `nlrc_vksplat_config.hpp` only (shader generator contract)
- `#pragma once`

Forbidden in new `next/` code:

- Function-like macros (`MIN`, `MAX`, `CLAMP`) — use `std::min`, `constexpr`, or templates
- Unscoped logic macros — prefer `inline constexpr` or `if constexpr`

C++ below `namespace nlrc::vksplat` in the config header:

- No `typedef` — use `using`
- `bool` for semantic on/off flags; `int` only for numeric shader parameters mirrored from `VKSPLAT_*`

## Types and APIs

- Prefer **`using`** over **`typedef`**
- Prefer **`enum class`** over unscoped `enum` (unless C/Vulkan ABI requires raw `enum`)
- Mark single-argument constructors **`explicit`** unless implicit conversion is intentional (add a brief comment)
- Apply **`[[nodiscard]]`** to getters, handles, and status/error returns
- Use **`override`** / **`final`** on virtual hierarchies; **`= default`** / **`= delete`** where appropriate
- No raw **`new`** / **`delete`** — RAII wrappers
- No C-style casts — `static_cast` / `reinterpret_cast` with justification
- Vulkan/pipeline code: see `rewrite-error-handling.mdc` for `check_vk` and `[[nodiscard]]` status wrappers

## Generated C++

- `*_spirv.hpp` is emitted only by `spirv_to_header()` in `scripts/compile_shaders.py` — never hand-edit
- Embed symbols: `k{Name}Spirv[]` and `k{Name}SpirvWordCount` in `nlrc::vksplat::shaders` — see `shader-build-embed.mdc`
- Generated headers must pass the same **clang-format** and **clang-tidy** checks as hand-written code (enforced at shader build time)

## Tooling

Naming follows [`.clang-tidy`](next/nlrc_vksplat/.clang-tidy); formatting follows [`.clang-format`](next/nlrc_vksplat/.clang-format).

Blocking lint:

- CMake target **`nlrc_vksplat_lint`** runs `scripts/lint_cpp.py` (clang-format `--Werror` + clang-tidy)
- **`nlrc_vksplat_core`** depends on lint — every build must pass
- Shader generation runs clang-format/tidy on each `*_spirv.hpp` before the build proceeds

After any C++ or `spirv_to_header()` change: configure preset, then `cmake --build --preset <preset>` (or `--target nlrc_vksplat_lint`).
